§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Suppose $X ⊂ 𝗥^d$ and $f: 𝗥^d → 𝗥$. ⦉

  ‖ An optimization problem $(X, f)$ is ❬convex❭ (a ❬convex
    optimization problem❭, ❬convex program❭, ❬ordinary convex
    program❭) if $X$ is a convex set and $f$ is a convex
    function. ⦉
